ogy and develops a new way to think about the nature of historical consciousness.Rather than seeing the present as either tragedy or farce, Schram argues that contemporary historical consciousness is produced through reflexive sociality. Like all societies, Auhelawa is located in an intercultural conjuncture, yet their contemporary life is not a story of worlds colliding, but a shattered mirror in which multiple Auhelawa subjectivities are possible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEthnologyzPapua New GuineazMilne Bay Province. 0aPostcolonialismzPapua New GuineazMilne Bay Province. 0aSocial changezPapua New GuineazMilne Bay Province. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aReligious Studies.  apostcolonial consciousness, Christianity, Oceania, cultural change.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060655308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060401608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2018z9783110603231oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171101540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501711015423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501711015/original  a978-3-11-060401-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-2